    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>Last post I sent <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0209">my map</title></bibl>
                    in hopes that the precincts of the <placeName ref="pl0711">Highlands</placeName>
                    may be justly traced. That returned to me at <placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName>, franked by <persName ref="pe0018">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Jackson</persName> who I trust has the power.
                    I flatter myself I made no mistake, for I think you s<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> I might send to him any overweight. I set off for home next week.
                    Thank you for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Letter but am too much hurried to
                    say more at present than</p>
                <closer><salute>I am D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir affectly yrs</salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                <dateline>April 23<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 1776.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
